IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO RECRUIT DIVERSE PHILANTHROPIC RESOURCES TO SUPPORT THE GOALS AND PROJECTS OF THE CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS FOUNDATION (CAFP-F) IS TO ADVANCE THE DELIVERY OF ACCESSIBLE, COMPASSIONATE AND COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE TO THE PEOPLE OF CALIFORNIA BY SUPPORTING THE GOALS AND PROJECTS OF THE CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS AND SECURING DIVERSE PHILANTHROPIC RESOURCES TO ACCOMPLISH THOSE GOALS.
IRS990.Desc: THE CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS FOUNDATION SUPPORTS MEDICAL STUDENT AND FAMILY MEDICINE ACTIVITIES SUCH AS THE FAMILY MEDICINE INTEREST GROUPS ON MEDICAL SCHOOL CAMPUSES, THE FAMILY MEDICAL SUMMIT FOR RESIDENTS, THE FUTURE FACES OF FAMILY MEDICINE PROGRAM, AND MEDICAL STUDENT RESEARCH EXTERNSHIPS. THE FOUNDATION SUPPORTS THE CALIFORNIA RESIDENCY NETWORK AND FM RESIDENTS. THE FOUNDATION ALSO FACILITATES MEETINGS AND DEVELOPS CONTINUING MEDICAL EDUCATION ACTIVES RELATED TO ADDRESSING A VARIETY OF CLINICAL ISSUES OF IMPORTANCE TO FAMILY PHYSICIANS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CAFP-FOUNDATION, IN CONJUNCTION WITH ITS PARENT THE CAFP, USES A MULTI-PERSON INTERNAL CONTROL STRUCTURE OF EMPLOYEES EITHER INVOLVED WITH THE PROGRAM OR NOT DESIGNED TO FACILITATE INSPECTION. REPORTING IS THEN PERIODICALLY PROVIDED TO THE GRANTOR FOR THEIR EVALUATION OF PROGRESS AND EXPENDITURE. FINALLY, BOTH THE CAFP AND THE CAFP-FOUNDATION ARE AUDITED BY AN INDEPENDENT, OUTSIDE AUDITOR.

THE CEO IS PAID FROM A RELATED ORGANIZATION, CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS. THE RELATED ORGANIZATION USES THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES TO ESTABLISH COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S CEO. COMPENSATION COMMITTEE, INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT, FORM 990 OF OTHER ORGANIZATIONS, WRITTEN EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT, AND APPROVAL OF THE BOARD OR COMPENSATION COMMITTEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENTIRE BOARD IS E-MAILED WITH AN ELECTRONIC DRAFT OF THE 990 PRIOR TO FILING. THE GOVERNING BOARD HAS DEPUTIZED THE SECRETARY-TREASURER, PRESIDENT, PRESIDENT-ELECT AND IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT TO REVIEW THE 990 IN DETAIL AND APPROVE FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PERSONS COVERED BY THIS POLICY WILL ANNUALLY DISCLOSE OR UPDATE TO THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES ON A FORM PROVIDED BY THE ORGANIZATION THEIR INTERESTS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST, SUCH AS A LIST OF FAMILY MEMBERS, SUBSTANTIAL BUSINESS OR INVESTMENT HOLDINGS, AND OTHER TRANSACTIONS OR AFFILIATIONS WITH BUSINESSES AND OTHER ORGANIZATIONS OF THOSE FAMILY MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO AND ALL EMPLOYEES ARE PAID FROM A RELATED ORGANIZATION, CALIFORNIA ACADEMY OF FAMILY PHYSICIANS. THE RELATED ORGANIZATION USES THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES: THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S PRESIDENT, IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT , AND PRESIDENT-ELECT ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. KEY EMPLOYEE'S COMPENSATION AND BONUSES ARE DETERMINED BY THE CEO, PURSUANT TO BUDGETARY PARAMETERS ESTABLISHED BY THE BOARD. THIS PROCESS WAS LAST UNDERTAKEN IN 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 1023, FORM 990 AND FORM 990-T, IF APPLICABLE, ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST. BOARD OF TRUSTEES AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MINUTES ARE KEPT IN PERPETUITY.
THE ORGANIZATION HAS A COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT AUDIT AND THE SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT.
